         <abstract>
            <p>For odd square-free &lt;latex&gt;$n &gt; 1$&lt;/latex&gt; the cyclotomic polynomial Φ&lt;sub&gt;n&lt;/sub&gt;(x) satisfies the identity of Gauss, 4Φ&lt;sub&gt;n&lt;/sub&gt;(x) = A&lt;sup&gt;2&lt;/sup&gt;&lt;sub&gt;n&lt;/sub&gt; - (-1)&lt;sup&gt;(n - 1)/2&lt;/sup&gt;nB&lt;sup&gt;2&lt;/sup&gt;&lt;sub&gt;n&lt;/sub&gt;. A similar identity of Aurifeuille, Le Lasseur, and Lucas is Φ&lt;sub&gt;n&lt;/sub&gt;((-1)&lt;sup&gt;(n - 1)/2&lt;/sup&gt;x) = C&lt;sup&gt;2&lt;/sup&gt;&lt;sub&gt;n&lt;/sub&gt; - nxD&lt;sup&gt;2&lt;/sup&gt;&lt;sub&gt;n&lt;/sub&gt; or, in the case that n is even and square-free, ±Φ&lt;sub&gt;n/2&lt;/sub&gt;(-x&lt;sup&gt;2&lt;/sup&gt;) = C&lt;sup&gt;2&lt;/sup&gt;&lt;sub&gt;n&lt;/sub&gt; - nxD&lt;sup&gt;2&lt;/sup&gt;&lt;sub&gt;n&lt;/sub&gt;. Here, A&lt;sub&gt;n&lt;/sub&gt;(x), ..., D&lt;sub&gt;n&lt;/sub&gt;(x) are polynomials with integer coefficients. We show how these coefficients can be computed by simple algorithms which require O(n&lt;sup&gt;2&lt;/sup&gt;) arithmetic operations and work over the integers. We also give explicit formulae and generating functions for A&lt;sub&gt;n&lt;/sub&gt;(x), ..., D&lt;sub&gt;n&lt;/sub&gt;(x), and illustrate the application to integer factorization with some numerical examples.</p>
          </abstract>
